<subsection xml:id="C24.S15.SS3">
<title>Stirling Numbers</title>        
 
  
<para xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="35" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p1.s1">
The Stirling numbers of the first kind <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p1.m1">s\left(n,m\right)</Math> , and the second kind <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p1.m2">S\left(n,m\right)</Math> , are as defined in ยง26.8(i).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="36" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="24.15.6" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S15.E6">B_{n}=\sum_{k=0}^{n}(-1)^{k}\frac{k!S\left(n,k\right)}{k+1},</Math> <Math equation-number="24.15.7" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S15.E7">B_{n}=\sum_{k=0}^{n}(-1)^{k}\genfrac{(}{)}{0.0pt}{}{n+1}{k+1}S\left(n+k,k \right)\bigg{/}\genfrac{(}{)}{0.0pt}{}{n+k}{k}</Math> ,, <Math equation-number="24.15.8" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S15.E8">\sum_{k=0}^{n}(-1)^{n+k}s\left(n+1,k+1\right)B_{k}=\frac{n!}{n+1}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="37" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p2.s1">
In (24.15.9) and (24.15.10)
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="38" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p2.s2">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p2.m1">p</Math> denotes a prime.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="39" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p2.s3">
SeeHorata (1991).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="40" xml:id="C24.S15.SS3.p2.s4">
<Math equation-number="24.15.9" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S15.E9">p\frac{B_{n}}{n}\equiv S\left(p-1+n,p-1\right)\pmod{p^{2}}, if 1\leq n\leq p-2,</Math> <Math equation-number="24.15.10" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S15.E10">\frac{2n-1}{4n}p^{2}B_{2n}\equiv{S\left(p+2n,p-1\right)\pmod{p^{3}}}, if 2\leq 2n\leq p-3</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C24.S15.SS4">
<title>Fibonacci and Lucas Numbers</title>        
  
 
<para xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="41" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.s1">
The Fibonacci numbers are defined by <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m1">u_{0}=0</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m2">u_{1}=1</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m3">u_{n+1}=u_{n}+u_{n-1}</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m4">n\geq 1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="42" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.s2">
The Lucas numbers are defined by <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m5">v_{0}=2</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m6">v_{1}=1</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m7">v_{n+1}=v_{n}+v_{n-1}</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.m8">n\geq 1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="43" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="24.15.11" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S15.E11">\sum_{k=0}^{\left\lfloor\ifrac{n}{2}\right\rfloor}{n\choose 2k}\left(\frac{5}{ 9}\right)^{k}B_{2k}u_{n-2k}=\frac{n}{6}v_{n-1}+\frac{n}{3^{n}}v_{2n-2},</Math> , <Math equation-number="24.15.12" mode="display" xml:id="C24.S15.E12">\sum_{k=0}^{\left\lfloor\ifrac{n}{2}\right\rfloor}{n\choose 2k}\left(\frac{5}{ 4}\right)^{k}E_{2k}v_{n-2k}=\frac{1}{2^{n-1}}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="44" xml:id="C24.S15.SS4.p2.s1">
For further information on the Fibonacci numbers see ยง26.11.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
